CO2-eq/kWh; median = 1,001) leading to confusion over reasonable
estimates of life cycle GHG emissions from coal-fired electricity
generation. By adjusting published estimates to common gross system
boundaries and consistent values for key operational input parameters
(most importantly, combustion carbon dioxide emission factor {[}CEF]),
the meta-analytical process called harmonization clarifies the existing
literature in ways useful for decision makers and analysts by
significantly reducing the variability of estimates (-53% in IQR
magnitude) while maintaining a nearly constant central tendency (-2.2%
