the area vulnerable to high- severity fire, with additional reductions of 4–7% depending on the prescription. However, increasing the extent of treat- ments reduced the extent of harmful downwind smoke impacts, primarily by reducing rate of fire spread. Treatment strategies will depend on specific management objectives, but we illustrate that trade- offs are not necessarily inherent in general outcomes of fuel treatments.},
