At some point, the fractal dimensions remain nearly constand, indicating a quasi-steady-state of fire propagation is reached (seems opposite of the conclusion of Calderelli wrt SODP). fractal dimensions of the perimeter is observed for density of vegetation p=0.6.


Notes:
Not sure how the fire is stopped, other than observed duration (is that really the biggest problem in fire modelling?). Uses lots of physics in the underlying equations. Clearly trying to replicate fire events. What's the purpose of the model? Intended applications not really clear.},
